article.description: Boise State edges past Air Force 77-68
article.headline: Boise State edges past Air Force 77-68
article.linkText: Boise State edges past Air Force 77-68
article.story: COLORADO SPRINGS, Colo. -- Derrick Marks scored 28 points and Nick Duncan added a career-high 20 to lead Boise State to a 77-68 victory over Air Force in a close contest on Saturday afternoon. The Falcons held a 31-30 lead at intermission. Boise State pulled ahead on Marks' 3-pointer -- the first shot of the second half -- and never trailed again, although the final 20 minutes saw five ties and no more than a single-digit lead. Marks shot 4 of 5 from 3-point range and had six assists. Duncan finished 6 of 8, all from beyond the arc for the Broncos, and James Webb III added 10 points and five steals. Boise State (14-6, 4-3 Mountain West) shot almost 58 percent from the floor, and 14 of 22 on 3-pointers. Marek Olesinski led Air Force (8-11, 1-7) with 24 points and 10 rebounds, and Hayden Graham chipped in 14 points.
